DOWNY MILDEW, MAIZE - BANGLADESH: (KHULNA)
******************************************

A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 30 Nov 2011
Source: New Age [edited]
http://newagebd.com/newspaper1/national/41821.html


Maize farmers face crop failure
-------------------------------
Maize farmers in Chuadanga district [Khulna division] have suffered
severe loss as a large cultivated area of hybrid corn failed to
produce any seeds. The growth of the plants suddenly stopped with
roots and branches coming out from the stems instead of producing
flowers.

Local department of agriculture [DAE] officials said the fields were
affected by 'downy mildew' disease. They said that there was no hope
of getting any crops from the affected plants and many of the farmers
have been cutting the plants as fodder for cattle.

The farmers who used 2 brands of seed were mostly affected by the crop
failure. Those who used other brands of hybrid seed were less affected
in the area. Seed companies took samples and photographs of the
plants.

The Seed Certification Authority said that they had just come to know
about the outbreak of the disease. DAE plant protection said that they
only conducted germination tests of the seed during import.

[Byline: Tapos Kanti Das]

